&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in procurement, with 2+ years in datacenter infrastructure operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of compute infrastructure components (servers, GPUs/TPUs, networking, storage)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing high-value, complex procurement relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of 2-way and 3-way match procure-to-pay processes and purchase order management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with procurement systems (Zip, Workday ERP, or similar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capital-intensive procurement experience with datacenter buildouts, power infrastructure, and understanding components of long-lead-time equipment procurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of process improvement and workflow optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical skills for vendor analysis, cost savings identification, and budget tracking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-functional collaboration experience working with diverse business stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growth company experience comfortable with ambiguity and rapid scaling environments&lt;/li&gt;
